<subSubSection id="B1B4654A33469533EB2AFEF6FEACFFF2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F91136C133469533EB2AFEF6FEACFFF2" blockId="3.[264,1323,284,510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="CBDAEAD333469533EB2AFEF6FE1FFF51" bold="true" box="[312,452,323,349]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the trifurcate mandibles, which are unique in the genus and readily distinguish it from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="3EAE4D4233469533E9BAFED9FB98FF89" box="[936,1091,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Sclerostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBDAEAD333469533E9BAFED9FB98FF89" box="[936,1091,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Sclerostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="CBDAEAD333469533EB2AFE26FE18FFA1" bold="true" box="[312,451,403,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species can be easily distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="3EAE4D4233469533EE45FE21FB29FFA1" box="[1111,1266,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Sclerostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CBDAEAD333469533EE45FE21FB29FFA1" box="[1111,1266,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Sclerostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the apical trifurcate mandibles and by the presence of a conspicuous tubercle on the frons.
</paragraph>
